<h2>Information  Collection</h2>
<p>Salem Health does not collect  personal information from the users of the Site. However, emailed requests and  inquiries are passed to the appropriate Salem Health personnel, who may retain  records in the ordinary course of business.</p>
<p>We are committed to protecting the  privacy of all, including children's privacy and do not intentionally collect  any information from children under the age of 13. If you are younger than 13,  please ask a parent or guardian for help in accessing and using the Site.</p>
<h2>Cookies</h2>
<p>&quot;Cookies&quot; are routinely  used by entities engaged in E-commerce, including Salem Health. A cookie is a  piece of data stored on a user's hard drive through the Web browser program  containing information about the user which enables us to track and personalize  the Site to enhance your online experience. You can avoid cookies by  configuring your browser to reject them or at least notify you when a cookie is  being placed on your hard drive.</p>
<h2>Log  Files</h2>
<p>Like most other online entities,  Salem Health collect technical information from a user's computer when that  user requests a Web page while visiting the Site. The information tells Salem  Health the user's Internet Protocol address, type of browser, the address of  any linking Web site, and other technical information. Salem Health  occasionally uses a third party to collect and analyze this information.  However, we do not sell or rent the information to any third party.</p>
